ExecDesc.value: Microsoft Office Excel BIFF5 Record Parsing Use After Free(IPv6 Version)

EngDesc.value: A use after free vulnerability exists in Microsoft Excel. The vulnerability is due to the way the vulnerable product parses ShrFmla BIFF records in Excel documents. A crafted Excel file could trigger an error condition which could result in accessing of freed memory. A remote attacker could exploit this vulnerability by enticing a target user to open a crafted Excel document. A successful attack could result in the execution of arbitrary code in the security context of the target user.
